name: Rainbow Veggie Chili
author: theveggieone
summary: Multi-colored vegetables make this chili delicious and pretty! Serve with cornbread for a great fall dinner.
ingredients: 1 (28 ounce) can crushed tomatoes, with liquid
1 (15 ounce) can black beans, drained and rinsed
1 (15 ounce) can whole kernel corn, drained
1 (15 ounce) can chili beans in spicy sauce, undrained
¼ teaspoon cayenne pepper, or to taste
directions: Heat oil in a large pot over medium-high heat
Stir in zucchini, yellow squash, red bell pepper, green bell pepper, jalapeno, garlic, and onion
Mix tomatoes with liquid, tomato paste, black beans, corn, and chili beans in spicy sauce into the pot
Season with chili powder, oregano, black pepper, and cayenne pepper
Reduce heat to low and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally
